President Cyril Ramaphosa will on Sunday participate in a 12km fun walk at the 33rd Annual Gandhi Walk in Lenasia, Johannesburg. The annual fundraiser, organised by the Gandhi Walk Committee (GWC), promotes community and health awareness. The theme for this year is “Going Green”, focused on championing social change and promoting community awareness, to change attitudes and behaviours towards climate change and greener living. The #GandhiWalk2018 will also raise awareness for the fight against Rhino poaching. Last month, the president participated in a 5km walk from the Gugulethu Sports Complex to Athlone Stadium. Other government officials who are participating in the in this year’s Gandhi Walk are Minister of Public Service and Administration Ayanda Dlodlo. #GandhiWalk2018 Minister of Public Service & Administration Ayanda Dlodlo at the 33rd annual Gandhi Walk in #Lenasia @FaizelPatel143 pic.twitter.com/PQ9yOqm6SC — Radio Islam (@radioislam) April 15, 2018  #GandhiWalk2018 @GandhiWalkLENZ @SANParksHR pic.twitter.com/23WGmBWG2n — Yusuf Abramjee (@Abramjee) April 15, 2018  #GandhiWalk2018 @GandhiWalkLENZ @ChangeAgentSA @CyrilRamaphosa pic.twitter.com/Pc8a1kBVUO — Yusuf Abramjee (@Abramjee) April 15, 2018  The central theme for Gandhi Walk 2018 is“Going Green” aimed to champion social change and promote community awareness to change attitudes and behaviours towards climate change and greener-living. @GovernmentZA @PresidencyZA @MinAyandaDlodlo #GandhiWalk2018 pic.twitter.com/XZnQsdQaAd — National DPSA (@thedpsa) April 15, 2018  -TNA Reporter